6.10	Islam_in_the_Republic_of_Macedonia	Islam in the Republic of Macedonia	Albanian Muslims, forming roughly 25% of the nation's total population and most of the Muslim population, live mostly in the Polog and western regions of the country. The Turks, who make up about 4% of the country's total population, are scattered throughout the country, but mostly in major cities, as are Roma Muslims. Bosniaks are mostly concentrated within Skopje. Muslims of Macedonian ethnicity number roughly 40,000 to 100,000 and can be found in western Macedonia in the Centar Å½upa, Debar, Struga and Plasnica areas.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/Tetovo_Bunte_Moschee.jpg/250px-Tetovo_Bunte_Moschee.jpg
